Two points...<P>1)<BR> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>  <B>5. STAY CLOSE to the mob to keep hate up.</B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE> <P>So few people realize the true power of proximity agro.  To test this, we put a warrior directly in front of a mob partially touching it, and armed him with a 2hander.  Then we put a rogue behind the mob, at the outer edge of its melee range.<P>The warrior initiated attack, and did not taunt.  The rogue BS'ed at will and never gained agro.  Good rule to apply.<P>2)<P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>  <B>2: Always, always kill the caster mobs first, then the meleers. Another thing that is over looked.<BR>4:If caster (such as cleric) gets hit, all attention goes to that mob until it is unaggroed from caster.<P></B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE> <P>I guess if you're group has no Enchanter, this is ok, but Enchanters love to ToT caster mobs.  All the groups I've been in, Caster mobs get dropped last, so I can steal their mana.<P>Also, any mob that agro's the Cleric, is the Enchanter's or Bard's or Necro's responsibilty, not the tanks.  Switching targets is devistating.<P>--------------------<P>Dominus<BR>Templars of Necrose<BR>Mith Marr<BR>56 Enchanter<BR>www.templarsofnecrose.com<BR>------------------<BR>Never fight with ugly people, they have nothing to lose.
