</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
If I am doing crowd control, you had better take the casters last.  This goes double if they are complete healers or gaters.  When it is low on health, the bard will be chain mezzing to interupt healing/gating, he can't do that if there is another mob or two that he is keeping locked down.<P>The only time you take casters first is if the group has no crowd control.  In that case, nuke hard near the end to stop complete heals and gates.<P>Dilbis Xll<BR>60th Human Bard<BR>Tarew Marr
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="1"  face="Verdana, Arial">
